Boil a large #pot of @salted water{} for the @baby potatoes{500%grams}.

Preheat the #oven (for the burger buns) to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve the baby potatoes (quarter larger potatoes).

When boiling, add the potatoes to the water, lower the heat to medium and cook until fork tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander and return to the pot, off the heat. Cover to keep warm.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Place a hand flat on top of the @Irish chicken breast{320%grams}. Slice through horizontally to make two thin steaks.

Place a large #pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Add the chicken. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Cook through, ~{3-6%minutes} each side.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is due to packaging we use to keep it fresh.

While the chicken fries, trim the @salad leaves{120%grams}, halve lengthways and thinly slice widthways.

Thinly slice the @tomato{1}.

To make your dressing, combine the @mayo{sachet} with salt, pepper, 1 tbsp of @oil{1%tbsp} and ½ tsp of @sugar{1/2%tsp} (double both for 4p) in a #medium bowl.

When the chicken is cooked, remove from the pan and set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Stir in the @honey{2%sachets} and @gochujang paste{1%sachet} (use less if you don't like spice).

Pour in @water{50%ml} (double for 4p), bring to the boil then reduce the heat. Simmer until thickened and sticky, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in 1 tbsp of @butter{1%tbsp} (double for 4p) until melted.

Return the chicken to the pan and turn to coat fully in the glaze.

While the glaze simmers, pop your @brioche buns{2} in the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

When the potatoes are ready, stir through the @paprika{sachet}, @BBQ sauce{sachet} and a knob of @butter{to taste}. Season with salt and pepper.

Toss the chopped salad leaves through the salad dressing.

When everything's ready, share the buns between plates.

Top the base buns with a handful of the chopped salad leaves and sliced tomato.

Load the glazed chicken on top then spoon over any remaining honey gochujang sauce then sandwich closed with the bun lids.

Serve the BBQ potatoes and remaining salad leaves and remaining tomato slices alongside.